{#
  Shared tier badge — Wave 1 of the UI redesign (2026-06-03).

  Unifies the three legacy tier-rendering systems (.tier-chip on Deals
  table, .card-tier on Today/Review attention cards, .paper-grade on
  the dossier verdict section). Wave 2 templates can adopt this
  partial; the legacy classes keep rendering unchanged until the
  backlog sweep migrates callers.

  This Wave-1 version renders as the existing .card-tier shape so the
  attention-card-card-meta context already styles it correctly. Wave 2
  may introduce a leaner .tier class with modifier --A / --B / --C /
  --D / --F if the bespoke per-context styling needs to consolidate;
  for now, the safest move is to reuse what's already styled.

  Inputs:
    tier  — string, one of "A" | "B" | "C" | "D" | "F" | None
            (lowercased and used as the modifier class)
    label — optional string under the tier letter (default "tier")

  Examples:
    {% include "_tier_badge.html.j2" with context %}  → "B tier"
    where caller sets `tier = "B"`.

  Behavior on tier=None: renders nothing. The calling template
  decides whether an absent tier shows a placeholder.
#}
{%- if tier -%}
<span class="card-tier tier-{{ tier|lower }}" title="Deal tier from score_deal">{{ tier }}<span class="card-tier-label">{{ label|default('tier') }}</span></span>
{%- endif -%}
